title: Bikewatching
description: I created a website that shows bike routes in Boston and Cambridge, MA, using the Mapbox API and publicly available bike route data. The website allows users to view and filter bike stations based on time of day, and shows when bike stations are most populated.

title: Mindful Snacking: Food Processing Data Visualization
description: I made a bar chart visualization of average food processing scores among five categories of snacks, from three different stores. Insights about mindful snacking can be drawn from this visualization, and it can be concluded that nuts and seeds have the lowest food processing score among the most popular snacks.

title: League of Legends Draft Analysis
description: I analyzed competitive match data from the 2024 League of Legends season, handling missing values, conducting hypothesis testing, and building a predictive model for game outcomes based on early-game data and team rosters.

title: Computer Vision-Based Driver Assistance System
description: I designed and implemented an advanced object detection system capable of recognizing vehicles, pedestrians, and other common road objects, with integrated lane marking identification.

title: TritonHacks 2024 - Game Development Starter Kit
description: I developed a starter project in Unity with a partner for a high school hackathon that served 85 attendees, with the starter kit including custom 3D models, scripting guides, and a customizable procedural terrain generation system.

title: Stock Prediction with Machine Learning
description: I collaborated with a partner to develop four machine learning models that predict future stock prices of various companies, and deployed a website to elegantly display the predictions, showing nuanced differences in the models.
